Mountain Center first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Mountain Center had a population of 66. The population density was {{convert|35.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Mountain Center was 51 (77%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 1 (2%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 1 (2%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 0 (0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 13 (20%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 9 persons (14%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Mountain Center CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0649544 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 39 households, out of which 2 (5%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 23 (59%) were married-couple households, 0 (0%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 3 (8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 13 (33%) had a male householder with no partner present. 9 households (23%) were one person, and 2 (5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.69.<ref name=DP1/> There were 27 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (69% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Mountain Center CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0649544 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 9 people (14%) under the age of 18, 1 people (2%) aged 18 to 24, 13 people (20%) aged 25 to 44, 29 people (44%) aged 45 to 64, and 14 people (21%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 54.3{{nbsp}}years. There were 35 males and 31 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 43 housing units at an average density of {{convert|22.8|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 39 (91%) were occupied. Of these, 27 (69%) were owner-occupied, and 12 (31%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

